data.mission: Run ONE canonical artifact verification script (use an existing `verify_artifacts.py` / `verify_build_artifacts.py` from `runtime/outputs/code-creation/...`) against the produced `runtime/_build/` directory and emit a machine-readable report to `runtime/_build/reports/verify_artifacts.json`. The verifier must hard-fail if required artifacts are missing or empty.

Run the existing preflight diagnostics script (e.g., `runtime/outputs/code-creation/**/preflight_diagnostics.py` or `preflight_smoke.py`) in the real execution environment and persist outputs to `runtime/_build/reports/preflight.json` and `runtime/_build/logs/preflight.log`, including Python version, cwd, repo root, permissions check for `runtime/_build/`, and a directory listing of `runtime/outputs/` and `runtime/_build/`.

Select ONE canonical runner among the already-created entrypoints (`run_pipeline.py`, latest `build_runner.py`, or `run_all.py` under `runtime/outputs/code-creation/**/`) and execute it end-to-end, forcing all artifacts into `runtime/_build/` (logs, reports, tables, figures). Save full stdout/stderr to `runtime/_build/logs/run.log` and write a machine-readable run summary to `runtime/_build/reports/run_summary.json` (step status, durations, exit code).

Execute the existing artifact verification script (`verify_build_artifacts.py` / `verify_artifacts.py` already created under `runtime/outputs/code-creation/**/`) against the newly-produced `runtime/_build/` directory; hard-fail on missing/empty required artifacts; persist verifier stdout/stderr to `runtime/_build/logs/verify.log` and write `runtime/_build/reports/verify_report.json` (pass/fail + missing paths + file sizes).

Write a one-page 'Slice v0.1' spec: target effect family (cognition–affect–decision), populations, task types, primary outcomes, exclusion rules, and a draft moderator codebook mapping directly to extraction columns.
